Durban - Eleven people have died after gunmen opened fire on a taxi in Ladysmith on Tuesday. According to reports from the scene gunmen ambushed a private security vehicle linked to the Klipriver Taxi Association at at the Matiwaneskop N11 intersection. Five people in the security vehicle comprising bodyguards from the security company and a taxi boss were shot dead. The Ladysmith Gazette reported that a taxi passing the incident lost control and crashed, killing six occupants. It was uncertain if any shots were fired at the taxi. The taxi that crashed were reportedly transporting teachers from a nearby school. This is a developing story. Daily News